The '''Sunda scimitar babbler''' ('''''Pomatorhinus bornensis''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Timaliidae]]. It is [[Endemism|endemic]] to  [[Sumatra]], [[Borneo]], and [[Malaysia]]. The Sunda scimitar babbler and the [[Javan scimitar babbler]] were previously grouped together as the '''chestnut-backed scimitar babbler'''.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Species Updates – IOC World Bird List|url=https://www.worldbirdnames.org/new/updates/species-updates/|access-date=2021-05-28|language=en-US}}</ref> Its natural [[habitat]]s are [[subtropical or tropical moist lowland forest]] and subtropical or tropical moist [[montane forest]].

